name: Mount Jefferson

trails_config.name: Caps Ridge Trail
trails_config.description: The shortest path to big alpine views, Caps Ridge ascends steeply over a series of rocky ‘caps’. This hard hike rewards with an open summit panorama and a thrilling above-treeline scramble for relatively little mileage.
trails_config.parking_info: Caps Ridge Trail Parking, Jefferson Notch Rd

trails_config.name: Six Husbands Trail
trails_config.description: An epic and demanding route that climbs via the Six Husbands Trail with its famous ladders and sheer ledges. This expert loop traverses wild Great Gulf terrain and requires an overnight or car spot for a safe return, showcasing Mount Jefferson’s most rugged side.

generated_description:
The Experience

Standing at 5712 feet, Mount Jefferson is a standout peak in New Hampshire. Known for its rugged and challenging terrain, it offers a quintessential hiking experience.

The Challenge

Hikers often choose the **Caps Ridge Trail**, a **5.0 mile** route gaining significant elevation. As part of the **NH48 4000-Footers**, it draws peak-baggers from across the region.

Peak Bagging Logic

**Peak Bagging Opportunity:** Consider connecting this hike with **Mount Adams**, which is just 1.7 miles away. Linking these peaks is a popular way to maximize your day on the trail.
